@startuml
title Case Study - ATN Remote Upload Module Cloud Bursting

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/deployment-diagram-style.iuml

actor "Service\nConsumers" as SC

node "ATN (On-Premises)" as ATN {
  component "Remote Upload Module\n(on-premises service)" as RUM_OP
  component "Automated\nScaling Listener" as ASL
}

cloud "Cloud Provider" as Cloud {
  package "Leased Ready-Made\nEnvironment" as RME {
    component "Remote Upload Module\n(cloud-based, redundant\nimplementation)" as RUM_CL
    component "Replicated cloud\nservice instances" as RUM_REP
  }
  component "Pay-Per-Use\nMonitor" as PPM
}

SC --> ASL : upload requests
ASL --> RUM_OP : (2) monitor consumer\nrequests
RUM_OP <.. RUM_CL : (1) redundant\ndeployment

ASL --> PPM : (3) divert excess\nrequests when on-prem\nthreshold exceeded
PPM --> RUM_CL : forward, track\nfor billing
RUM_CL ..> RUM_REP : (4) on-demand\nresource replication

note right of RUM_CL
  When usage decreases, "burst in" is
  invoked: cloud service instances are
  released and no additional cloud usage
  fees are incurred.
end note

note bottom of ATN
  Original problem: on-premises Remote
  Upload Module rejected uploads at
  capacity, blocking deadline-sensitive
  document archival.
end note

@enduml
